> Treat your taste buds to a trip—no passport required! This riff on a classic French dish
>—duck a l’orange—features quick-cooking chicken cutlets in a jammy orange sauce. The saucy,
> savory-sweet meat is paired with thyme-infused mashed potatoes and crisp roasted green
>beans for a restaurant-worthy meal that's ready in just 35 minutes from start to finish.

== Thyme-Scented Mashed Potatoes ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Strip thyme leaves
from stems until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4 servings); roughly chop leaves.
Save a few remaining thyme sprigs for the next step. Halve @orange{1}.

Place potatoes and reserved thyme sprigs in a #medium pot{} with enough
@salt{} water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until potatoes
are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Carefully remove and discard thyme sprigs. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking
liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot off heat.

Mash potatoes with @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon}
until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid
as needed. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Green Beans ==

While potatoes cook, toss @green beans{6%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with
a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== Chicken & Orange Sauce ==

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and
season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} (use a large pan for 4 servings)
over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked
through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

While chicken cooks, squeeze juice from orange halves into a #small bowl{}.
Whisk in @apricot jam{2%tablespoon}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, chopped
@thyme{¼%ounce}(roughly chopped), half the @red wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}
(4 for 4 servings), and @water{2%tablespoon} (¼ cup for 4) until smooth.

Once chicken is done, return same pan to medium-high heat. Pour in sauce
and bring to a simmer; cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.
Stir in 1 TBSP @butter{} (2 TBSP for 4) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Return chicken to pan and turn a few times to coat.

== To Serve ==

Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and roasted green beans between plates.
Top chicken with any remaining sauce from pan and serve.